                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bowen has protested orally and in writing, as instructed. Probably only
                    effect will be to prevent Venezuelan Government from attacking other foreign
                    corporations for the present.</p>
                <p>It has come to his knowledge that the object of the Venezuelan President is to
                    recover from foreigners the amount he must pay to, them on their claims.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
